The authors did not compare the proposed method with their previous methods. The authors mentioned that the reason is that the previous methods address the problem of performance tuning. Performance tuning is to find the best configuration with the best performance. Performance prediction is to predict the best configuration with the best performance. In all the datasets in the evaluation, all configuration values are available or be calculated. So it seems performance tuning and performance prediction should be facing the same data. So what is the difference between performance tuning and performance prediction?
Is it possible to directly applying the previous method by the authors, like ActGan, to performance prediction?
